The paper discusses a technique for reconstructing 3D shapes using structured light, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The technique involves analyzing the motion blur of projected patterns, which could also fall under graphics (cs.GR) or robotics (cs.RO) subcategories. The use of video projectors and analysis of light flows could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories.
